            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">1. What counts as a Monthly Active User (MAU)</h4>
              <p>An MAU is a <strong>unique end user who authenticates at least once during a calendar month</strong>. A user is counted only once per month no matter how many times they sign in. Token refreshes, session introspections, and background token validations do <strong>not</strong> create additional MAUs.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">2. Authentication fair-use limit</h4>
              <p>Plans assume typical interactive usage of up to <strong>~30 authentications per MAU per month</strong> (a normal app averages well under 10). Sustained usage above this may be subject to overage of <strong>$0.002 per additional authentication</strong>. We will always notify you before any overage applies — there are no surprise charges.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">3. Machine-to-machine (M2M) tokens</h4>
              <p>Automated, service-to-service token issuance (OAuth <em>client-credentials</em> and similar non-human traffic) is <strong>billed separately</strong> from MAU, since it doesn't map to a human user. Talk to us for M2M / API token pricing tailored to your volume.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">4. Abuse &amp; automated traffic</h4>
              <p>Credential-stuffing, bot, scraping, or otherwise abusive authentication traffic may be rate-limited and is excluded from fair-use allowances. Our AI-powered monitoring flags anomalous patterns and protects your tenant automatically.</p>
            </div>
